						<summary>

						<p>This is a fragment of a bigger inscription in Vaṭṭeḻuttu alphabet, recording the gift of a <hi rend="italic">mā</hi> and half of land and 100 sheep to provide for the <hi rend="italic">ardhayāma</hi> (midnight) service and for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tirutturutti-Mahādēva. The donor's name is not known. Perumūr in Aṇḍa-nāḍu and another village Pāṇḍiyūr are mentioned.</p>						

						</summary>
